description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Theatre Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;34.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benenden Hospital require a Senior Theatre Practitioner to work in our modern and well-equipped theatres. As a private hospital, set in the heart of the Weald of Kent, you would be joining a hospital rated as ‘Outstanding’ by the CQC. Our recent multi-million pound redevelopment has transformed the services we can offer patients and this is a fantastic opportunity to join our outstanding team,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Theatre Practitioner will plan and Implement high standards of perioperative care for patients promoting a patient –focussed approach to care. You will also be responsible for planning, preparing and facilitating theatre lists, and ensuring patient areas are safe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for this position, it is essential that you have the following skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- First level Registered Nurse/ HCPC registered ODP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Post registration education in a relevant speciality, degree in Operating Department Practice, or 5+ years equivalent experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Expert Scrub Nurse with post qualification scrub experience in a range of surgical specialities including orthopaedics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Strong communication, negotiation and interpersonal skills to build and support team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Strong patient centred approach&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would also be an advantage to have the following attributes and qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Surgical First Assistant qualification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Basic computer skills e.g. MS Outlook, Excel, Word and web based reporting systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Excellent organisational planning and problem solving skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Proven experience in providing support and mentorship to more junior roles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rewards and benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Competitive salary, including an element of performance related pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- 27 days annual leave entitlement plus Bank Holidays, rising with service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Generous defined contribution pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Excellent Life Assurance benefit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free Membership of Benenden Health for Permanent Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free parking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Subsidised eye tests&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Enhanced Maternity pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free Flu vaccinations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Free tea and coffee&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Subsidised on site Restaurant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Active social club&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Benenden Hospital we take great pride in the quality of our staff promoting a friendly and supportive work place where people are given the right opportunities to succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To attract staff of the highest calibre, we offer excellent working conditions and facilities, promoting flexible working and a healthy home/work life balance. We are committed to professional development and have excellent training and education facilities in a safe and respectful environment. We work hard to make sure that everyone in Benenden feels involved and share our values and vision for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
